# Aerolab MCP Server

`aerolab mcp` runs a [Model Context Protocol](https://modelcontextprotocol.io/) server that exposes every aerolab subcommand as an MCP tool. It is implemented in:

- `src/cli/cmd/v1/cmdMcp.go` ‚Äî thin CLI entry point, wires flags into `pkg/mcp`
- `src/pkg/mcp/` ‚Äî the actual server: tool registration, argv building, subprocess execution, help rendering, gating, and transport

End-user documentation lives at `docs/mcp.md`. Keep that file in sync whenever you change behavior visible to an agent (tool names, profiles, flags, JSON schema, error messages).

## Architectural rules

1. **Self-introspection only** ‚Äî tool definitions must come from `BuildCommandTree(&Commands{})` in `cli/cmd/v1` and the `ParameterInfo` type. Do **not** hand-maintain a tool list in `pkg/mcp`.
2. **One-way dependency** ‚Äî `pkg/mcp` may not import `cli/cmd/v1`. Conversion from `CommandInfo`/`ParameterInfo` into `mcp.Command`/`mcp.Param` happens inside `cmdMcp.go`. If you need new command metadata, add it to both sides and to the converter.
3. **Subprocess execution** ‚Äî every tool call must fork the configured aerolab binary via `pkg/mcp.Runner`. Never exec commands in-process. This is what gives us isolation, timeouts, and bounded output.
4. **No writes to stdout in stdio mode** ‚Äî stdin/stdout belong to the MCP JSON-RPC stream. All diagnostics must go to stderr. `McpCmd.Execute` must not print status when `--transport=stdio`.
5. **Destructive gating** ‚Äî a command is destructive when `Command.Destructive == true` or when `IsDestructive()` matches its leaf name. Auto-registered tools must include `confirm` and `timeout_sec` in the schema, and `autoHandler` must call `Gate.Check` before executing.

## Adding a new tool

Prefer adding a new aerolab subcommand (struct + `Execute` method under `cli/cmd/v1/`). It will be picked up automatically. Write a hand-written MCP tool only if it does something genuinely outside the CLI (e.g. cross-command workflows). Place these in `pkg/mcp/tools_*.go` and register them from `NewServer`.

## Adding a new flag to McpCmd

1. Add the field with `long:` / `description:` / `default:` tags on `McpCmd`.
2. Parse/validate it in `runServer` before building `aerolabmcp.Config`.
3. Extend `aerolabmcp.Config` and thread the value to the place that consumes it (runner, gate, HTTP handler, ‚Ä¶).
4. Update `docs/mcp.md` (Flags table and any relevant section).

## Dynamic choices

Parameters with `webchoice:"method::List"` become `enum` values in the JSON Schema **only when `--init-backend` is used and the backend is available**. The server must never panic if a dynamic `List()` method fails ‚Äî `convertParamsForMCP` wraps the call in `safeResolveChoices`, which `recover()`s from panics and swallows errors. Keep that wrapper in place.

## Tests

- `pkg/mcp/*_test.go` covers schema, help, runner, gate, generic tools, auto tools, and auth. Run `go test ./pkg/mcp/...` after any change.
- When changing behavior visible to a model (tool count, destructive set, error strings), extend the relevant test rather than deleting it.

## Gotchas

- `go-flags.PrintHelp` calls `os.Exit`; never use it from MCP code. Use `RenderHelpFromFactory` ‚Üí `parser.WriteHelp(io.Writer)` instead.
- `exec.Cmd.Env` replaces the parent environment completely. `Runner.Execute` starts from `os.Environ()` and appends overrides ‚Äî keep that order.
- Auto-tool names are sanitized to match `^[A-Za-z_][A-Za-z0-9_-]*$`. If you change `AutoToolName`, update `tools_auto_test.go` and `docs/mcp.md`.
